When Lucifer Box Esq - dandy, rake, portraitist and His Majesty's Most Dashing Secret Agent - wrote the first volume of his adventures, The Vesuvius Club, he could never have imagined that one hundred and one years later he would end up as an artwork himself. But - like Dorian Grey before him - he has. Inspect Box at home in Number 9 Downing Street (but try to ignore the mess) and in the Turkish Baths. Witness his coach-chase though London, on the path of the murderer of Britain's most eminent scientific brains. Spy on the secrets he uncovers when that path leads him to Naples, including the biggest secret of all - the nefarious (but nice) Vesuvius Club.

On reading Mark Gatiss's novel, Stephen Fry exclaimed 'More, I want more!' Well here it is. A book that might just match the wildest dreams of its hero, The Vesuvius Club: The Graphic Edition illustrates Lucifer Box deliciously sandwiched between Edwardian low life and high society.
name: The Graphic Edition

Contents:

Batman #4 - Face The Court

Batman discovers the Court of Owls have hidden bases in buildings all over town belonging to the Wayne family. Last issue, Bruce sets off a tripwire in one and is blasted out of the 13th floor. This issue, we find him lured deep into subterranean Gotham, where he finally faces... The Court!

Batman and Gaucho get their man in South America then turn their attention to England, where they pair up with Batwoman and new recruit The Hood to fight against Dr Dedalus - Â­whose insane scheme threatens to bring the world to its knees...

description:
Final Issue

Contents:

Batman has been lured into the The Court of Owls' labyrinthine depths. The evil Talon pushes him to breaking point. His own history is dismantled before him, but clinging onto sanity, will he find the strength to fight back?

The Court of Owls has sentenced Batman to death...But first they'd like to play with their prey! The Talon beats four bells out of Batman at the behest of the Court. But just how many 'Talons' will he need to beat?

Batwoman faces the final showdown with The Weeping Woman alone. Able to dredge up Kate's deepest pain, this ghostly demon holds a deathly sway over our hero. Hold on to your cowls for this powerful conclusion.
